other_tests.findings: Tacky mucosal membranes. Abdomen: Soft. Tender to palpation in the right hemi-abdomen. Negative signs on physical exam, no masses, bowel sounds present, no guarding, rebound, or other signs indicating peritonitis.
Normal cardiomediastinal and hilar contours. Lungs are clear without consolidation or pulmonary edema. No pleural effusion or pneumothorax.
